      <h2>Pad Changes</h2>

      <h3>Replacing the Backing Pad</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Disconnect power.</li>
        <li>Insert the pad wrench (17 mm) between the backing pad and brake seal to hold the spindle nut.</li>
        <li>Turn the backing pad counterclockwise to remove it.</li>
        <li>Fit and tighten the new backing pad with washers.</li>
        <li>Remove the pad wrench.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="note">
        <strong>Pad Savers:</strong> Mirka pad savers placed between the backing pad and sanding disc protect the backing pad from wear during aggressive sanding with net products. Change them regularly to prolong backing pad life.
      </div>

      <h3>Replacing the Brake Seal</h3>
      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Too much vacuum</strong> in your dust extraction system may cause the brake seal to malfunction.
      </div>
      <ol>
        <li>Remove the backing pad as described above.</li>
        <li>Pull the old brake seal out of its groove.</li>
        <li>Fit the new brake seal in the groove.</li>
        <li>Fit the backing pad as described above.</li>
        <li>Check brake seal function. Adjust by changing the number of washers between the spindle and backing pad.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Speed Settings</h2>
      <p>The DEROS 350XCV has a variable speed range of 4,000 to 10,000 RPM.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Adjusting max RPM:</strong> Press the <strong>RPM+</strong> or <strong>RPM&ndash;</strong> button. Each press increases or decreases by 1,000 RPM.</li>
        <li><strong>Lever control:</strong> Speed varies linearly with lever position, from 4,000 RPM up to the set maximum.</li>
        <li><strong>Fixed speed mode:</strong> Press <strong>RPM+</strong> and <strong>RPM&ndash;</strong> simultaneously to toggle between variable (lever-controlled) and fixed speed modes. In fixed mode, the tool runs at the set max RPM whenever the lever is pressed.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Dust Extraction</h2>
      <p>For maximum performance, use the DEROS with a Mirka dust extractor (or other suitable unit) and Mirka net sanding products. This combination is the basis of Mirka's dust-free sanding solution.</p>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/workshop/manuals/mirka-deros-350x/p10_03.png" alt="Diagram showing dust extraction hose connection and airflow path on the DEROS 350XCV" />
        <figcaption>Dust extraction setup</figcaption>
      </div>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/workshop/manuals/mirka-deros-350x/p10_04.png" alt="DEROS 350XCV operation diagram showing proper sander positioning and dust extraction connection" />
        <figcaption>Operation and dust extraction overview</figcaption>
      </div>
      <ul>
        <li>Connect the dust extraction hose to the swivel exhaust port on the sander.</li>
        <li>Connect the sander's power cord to the outlet on the dust extractor to use its autostart function.</li>
        <li>Clean or replace the dust extractor's collection bag daily for optimum performance and to reduce combustion risk.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Operation</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Make sure the sander is switched off. Select a suitable abrasive and secure it to the backing pad, centered.</li>
        <li>Switch on the sander by pressing the <strong>On/Off</strong> key. The right LED turns green.</li>
        <li>Start sanding by pressing the lever. Adjust speed by varying lever position.</li>
        <li><strong>Always place the sander on the work surface before starting.</strong> Always remove the sander from the surface before stopping. This prevents gouging from excess abrasive speed.</li>
        <li>When finished, turn off the sander by pressing the <strong>On/Off</strong> key. The right LED turns off.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Bluetooth</h3>
      <p>The DEROS is equipped with Bluetooth Low Energy and can connect to the Mirka MyMirka app for additional functionality.</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Connect the power cord to the mains outlet.</li>
        <li>Press and hold the <strong>Speed+</strong> button while switching on with the <strong>On/Off</strong> button.</li>
        <li>The left LED lights up green, indicating Bluetooth is active.</li>
        <li>Bluetooth is deactivated when the tool is disconnected from the mains outlet.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Maintenance</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Always disconnect power before performing any maintenance.</strong>
      </div>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Backing pad:</strong> Replace when worn. Only use original Mirka backing pads designed for optimal performance with the brake seal. Never mount a backing pad without a spacer washer.</li>
        <li><strong>Brake seal:</strong> Replace if the brake seal does not function properly. See the Pad Changes section above.</li>
        <li><strong>Air vents:</strong> Keep the cooling air vents on the housing clean and free of blockages to ensure proper air circulation.</li>
        <li><strong>Abrasives:</strong> Do not use backing pads with a working speed below 10,000 RPM free speed.</li>
        <li><strong>Service:</strong> Any maintenance requiring the motor housing to be opened must be performed by an authorized Mirka service center.</li>
      </ul>

