      <h3>Vibration Reduction with Pad Saver or Interface</h3>
      <p>When using a pad saver or interface, vibration levels may increase. The DEROS 350X (77 mm models) does not require additional balancing screws. If using an interface, it is recommended to set the maximum speed to 7,000 RPM.</p>

      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Possible Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Right LED flashes red/green</td>
            <td>Connected to wrong mains voltage</td>
            <td>Connect to a mains outlet matching the tool's nominal voltage (100&ndash;120 VAC)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>No light from right LED when switched on</td>
            <td>Power cord not properly attached</td>
            <td>Check that the power cord is properly connected to both the sander and the mains socket</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Right LED is red and sander slows to 4,000 RPM</td>
            <td>Temperature too high; too heavy long-term load</td>
            <td>Reduce the load and allow the sander to cool; it will speed up again</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Right LED is red and RPM slightly reduced</td>
            <td>Too heavy short-term load</td>
            <td>Use lighter pressure; LED will automatically change back to green</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Brake seal does not work</td>
            <td>Worn brake seal or damaged spindle bearing</td>
            <td>Check and replace brake seal or spindle bearing</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Sander stopped and right LED is red</td>
            <td>Safety mode due to high temperature</td>
            <td>Wait until the tool has cooled down before resuming</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

